# Install to main Applications folder

When building, installing, or copying a macOS app (e.g. `.app` bundles):

- **Always** use the **main** Applications folder: `/Applications`
- **Never** use the user Applications folder: `~/Applications`
- **Always build and install after finishing code gen**: When you finish generating or changing code for an app in this project, run the full build and install (e.g. `make` or build the app, then `make install`). Do not leave the user to build or install manually.

Use `sudo` if required to copy into `/Applications`. Keep the project’s install target (e.g. Makefile `INSTALL_DIR`) set to `/Applications`.
